python
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

# Define the reference date
ref_date = datetime.strptime('2021-09-01', '%Y-%m-%d')

# Calculate the date 10 days ago
prev_date = ref_date - timedelta(days=10)

# Format the output in MM/DD/YYYY
formatted_date = prev_date.strftime('%m/%d/%Y')
print(formatted_date)
